Sep 23 2009 	Convenient location good value	We chose this hotel because we wanted to be near the Fremont Street Experience. Our room was very small but clean and updated with modern decor. This is an old hotel and the plumbing showed it. The toilet was an issue. The bathroom was very small and would not fit a standard toilet with tank. The toilet was similar to what you see in a public restroom. The flush handle was located behind the lid therefore the lid had to be closed first in order to get to the handle and had to be flushed several times after each use. The bathroom seemed to be put together in haste. The sink was tilted back and the sink stopper stayed closed, we had to pull it out completely to allow the sink to drain. The air conditioner in the room could not be controlled and was cold at times. It was also quite loud but this turned out to be a blessing as our room was located directly above the Fremont Street Experience which was quite loud. The air conditioner served as &quot;white noise&quot; to block out the sounds of the street below. I was surprised to find the room had plantation shutters instead of black out drapes but the shutters worked well enough blocking out the light. These are not five star accommodations but we were quite pleased with the price and the modern decor. I was really impressed at how friendly and happy all of the staff at the Fremont were. We ate dinner at Tony Roma's which was quite good. The buffet is typical of the buffets of old Las Vegas, not very good. We had breakfast there. Not a lot of choices but you can have an omelet made to order and your coffee cup is kept full and again the staff were all friendly. We went in all of the casinos downtown and in our opinion the Fremont gave the friendliest customer service and was the only casino that we could find a cocktail waitress taking orders for comp drinks.	
