Sep 12 2009 	Decent enough basic accomodations	I've stayed at the Fremont many times and know what to expect by now. Rooms are basic, clean but nothing fancy. The TV gets very few channels - the locals, CNN, ESPN, TBS, Weather Channel and that's about it I think. There's an in-room safe (with a key, not a combination) which is always good to have in LV. I've noticed that there are no longer any comforters on the beds, just a very light blanket. I find it hard to sleep without something heavier covering me. It's also just about the only hotel-casino in Las Vegas without a self-parking lot - it's valet only which I don't really care for, although service from the valet was good enough. The hotel doesn't provide any kind of high speed internet access. I was able to connect to some kind of general-use wireless access provided by a well-known travel site, but it didn't work that well, very frequent service interruptions.Buffet is average but cheap. Tony Roma's is good (although I didn't get to go this trip). Casino has some decent games but I always seem to have bad luck gambling there.	
Aug 25 2009 	Sam Boyd's Fremont Hotel and Casino	The property itself is old but extremely clean and safe. The casino restroom is brightly lit and very clean. The guest room is somewhat spartan but who stays in the room aside from sleeping or a quick rest in Vegas? It seems like Fremont's housekeeping department has very high standards--the guest room we occupied was extremely clean! Also, the towels and toiletries were provided generously. And no strands of hair or debris of any sort! You always felt safe on the casino floor especially if you are accompanying an elderly spouse because the hotel security is quite good. You can always spot a security officer, but they are never in your face. The hotel staff are all courteous and very helpful--they are not pushy and will always assist you when you ask for help. The properties on downtown Vegas are old, but the Fremont Hotel and Casino is very clean and safe place. Not too fancy like the strip but very dandy and fun. The hotel restaurant features a decent buffet so you really don't have to leave the property for anything! And the pricing at both the restaurant and cafeteria--not bad at all! The biggest asset of this hotel is safety! Never a bad experience!	
