Feb 10 2008 	Nice hotel and casino- Great Value!!	Okay okay, I know the Golden Nugget is the &quot;best&quot; place to stay downtown. But with the prices they were charging, I decided to go with the Fremont for about half. Well let me say that we came here from two nights at the Flamingo and this was a welcome change! The whole property has recently been redone. Everything is kind of retro-modern in the decor. The rooms were in very nice shape and the casino and lobby areas were clean, fresh, and nicely decorated. I was really impressed.We checked in early, they had a room for us immediately. Do not be expecting any 'views' from the hotel, but we could see Binion's out our window and part of the Fremont Street Experience. The windows opened, too which was very useful. The room is on the small side, but plenty for two people. Bathroom is admittedly cramped, but functional. The food at the Buffet is above average in my opinion, and for the price it has real value. Dinner was $28 for me and my hubby. They had made to order steaks, a carving station, wide selection of seafood and fish, desserts, etc. We ate here twice. The Lenai Express place had some Asian dishes and quickie type food. We also ate at Tony Roma's, again great, and between 4:30 and 7:30 they have a full prime rib dinner for $8! Very good and again great value. Oh and don't miss the $1 margarita's at the casino bar!Downtown Vegas itself has pros and cons. The police are out everywhere, so as long as you stick to the main &quot;drag&quot; you will be safe. That being said, there are more &quot;undesirables&quot; hanging around the casinos than on the strip. I am not a prejudiced or snobby person, but you can tell when a homeless guy gets a buck and comes and sits next to you at a slot. But again, security in the casinos was great, and a once I saw a pit boss ask a guy to leave cause he was sleeping at the blackjack table. Considering the price and the actual size of the property, I was really happy with our stay here. The casino was larger than I thought it would be and even larger than some of the neighboring hotels (Las Vegas Club, 4 Queens). Comparing the Fremont to the other hotels nearby, I am glad I decided to stay here. Everything was new, fresh, service was great and I took some money home! Will stay here again if we decide to visit Downtown Vegas on our next trip.	
Feb 3 2008 	good experience at the Fremont	stayed at the Fremont the last time in vegas. We have always loved the downtown area- it has the feel of living in a small town very close to a huge city. The fremont was clean &amp; the rooms are very small but functional. There are tub/shower combos in the rooms. We got a very good deal on the room (like $32 a night). Ate at the Second Street Grill- the steaks were very good &amp; the setting was dark &amp; romantic. The cost was under $100 for meal, a drink &amp; spilt a dessert. Also, ate breakfast at the buffet- it was decent for a regular breakfast.The Fremont even took care of us when our flight was cancelled &amp; we had to stay an extra night.	
