Nov 26 2006 	Mahala Baby!	What a well kept secret! I haven't visited Downtown Vegas since the neon cowboy's arm actually moved and said &quot;Howdy Partner&quot;! But, when all the Strip hotels were either booked or very overpriced this Thanksgiving weekend, I took a chance and looked at the hotels downtown, which are now part of the Fremont Experience. This is one of the original old school Las Vegas hotels built in 1956. I imagine this hotel has had several renovations over the past 50 years, but there has been a recent renovation just two months ago. And, it is a huge success! The guest rooms are decorated nicely into a tropical resort theme featuring most notably, white planation shutters on the windows. Usually those older hotels have a some-what overpowering odor from all the years of tobacco users puffing away inside. This hotel has been very well rid of that particuar problem and doesn't have that lingering sensory issue. I noticed that our Hawaiian brothers and sisters have found their way to this hotel in masses. I know that Las Vegas is one of the most preferred vacation destinations for our Hawaiian travelers. So, the Hawaiians can't all be wrong! Also, when you walk out onto the Fremont area, it is fantastic the way the street was closed and transformed into an area filled with lights, music, and life where visitors can experience a block-party atmosphere while walking between the adjacent hotels, casinos, outdoor vending carts and businesses. I can't wait to visit the Fremont again and bring new friends to enjoy the experience!	
